  "body": "## üéâ Description\r\n\r\nI was thinking it would be nice to have some simple inflationary token contracts in the zeppelin repo. This an issue to go along with a PR #815 for a discrete inflation calculation. The the owner will be able to set a time interval to be used for calculating inflation and minting new tokens along with a rate for that time period. For example 1 hour & 0.001%. The owner will then be able to call the ```mintTokens``` function periodically and mint new tokens. \r\n\r\nExample of initializing the token contract:\r\n```\r\n    lastInflationCalc = now;\r\n    inflationRatePerInterval = 1 hours;\r\n    timeInterval = 1000010880216701200; // 10% annual\r\n```\r\n```mintTokens``` function will throw if 1 hour has not elapsed since last update. If multiple hours have elapsed it will compute inflation for the whole time period.\r\n\r\nreference contract: https://github.com/relevant-community/contracts/blob/master/contracts/InflationaryToken.sol\r\n\r\n- [ ] üêõ This is a bug report.\r\n- [x] üìà This is a feature request.\r\n",
